'''Ōshima Shrine / Okutsushima Shrine''' (おおしまじんじゃおくつしまじんじゃ / おきつしまじんじゃ, '''Ōshima–Okutsushima Shrine''') is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945}} located in Kitatsuda-chō, {{ill|lt=Ōmihachiman City|Q385461|WD=Q385461}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|WD=Q131358}}. It consists of '''Ōshima Shrine''' and '''Okutsushima Shrine''', both of which are {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=UNKNOWN|WD=Q134917286}}. The former shrine rank was {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Prefectural Shrine|1=UNKNOWN}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
*{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ōkuninushi-no-Kami|1=UNKNOWN}} (Ōshima Shrine)
*{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Okutsushimahime-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}} (Okutsushima Shrine)

=== Shrine crest ===
Tortoiseshell floral diamond

=== History ===
According to shrine tradition, it was enshrined by {{ill|lt=Takenouchi no Sukune|Q1073668|WD=Q1073668}} during the reign of {{ill|lt=Emperor Seimu|Q316672|WD=Q316672}}. Ōshima Shrine and Okutsushima Shrine were originally enshrined at separate locations, but were relocated to the same site prior to the 6th year of {{ill|lt=Enbun|Q1145071|WD=Q1145071}} ({{ill|lt=1361|Q6159|WD=Q6159}}). Ōshima Shrine is classified as a Shikinaisha minor shrine, while Okutsushima Shrine is a {{ill|lt=Myōjin Taisha|Q9610964|WD=Q9610964}} {{ill|lt=disputed shrine|Q135022904|WD=Q135022904}}. According to the '{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Sandai Jitsuroku|1=UNKNOWN}}', in the first year of {{ill|lt=Jōgan (Japan)|Q1075635|WD=Q1075635|lt=Jōgan}} ({{ill|lt=859|Q23897|WD=Q23897}}), it was granted the divine rank of Junior Fifth Rank Upper Grade.

In the 3rd year of {{ill|lt=Taishō|Q329174|WD=Q329174}} ({{ill|lt=1914|Q2083|WD=Q2083}}), it was designated as a Prefectural Shrine.

=== Auxiliary and branch shrines ===
* Within the precincts
** Hifure Shrine
** Hiyoshi Shrine
** Shinomiya Shrine
** Kisai Shrine
** Gyōji Shrine
** Hakusan Shrine
** Aya Shrine
* Outside the precincts
** Ikejina Shrine
** Wakamikoshi Shrine
** Ame Shrine
** Wakamiya Shrine
** Dōdō Shrine

=== Festivals ===
* Torch Festival – held on April 17.
* Annual Festival – held on April 18.

=== Cultural properties ===
=== Important Cultural Properties (national designation) ===
* Seated wooden statue of Ōkuninushi-no-Mikoto (Sculpture) – Heian period work. Designated September 2, 1909 (Meiji 42)<ref>{{National Cultural Properties Database|201|3328|Seated Wooden Statue of Ōkuninushi-no-Mikoto}}</ref>.
* Chrysanthemum mother-of-pearl inlaid saddle, black lacquered saddle, black lacquered stirrups (Crafts) – Late Heian to Kamakura period works. Designated June 9, 1981 (Shōwa 56)<ref>{{National Cultural Properties Database|201|7223|{Chrysanthemum Mother-of-Pearl Inlaid Saddle (front ring missing) / Black Lacquered Saddle / Black Lacquered Stirrups}}}</ref>.
* Ōshima and Okutsushima Shrine documents (222 items): 1 scroll, 32 volumes, 3 sheets (Calligraphy) – Documents from the Kamakura to Edo periods. Designated June 6, 1987 (Shōwa 62)<ref>{{National Cultural Properties Database|201|9093|Ōshima and Okutsushima Shrine Documents (222 items)}}</ref>.

